channel.title: Compiling a .java to .class -.-
channel.description:
So, I decompiled the .class to a .java. Edited the IP only & then tried to compile it back into a .class.
Whenever I write javac client.java, it shows a whole load of errors which I didn't even touch.
Help? =(

item.title: Compiling a .java to .class -.-
item.dc:creator: @MeeE59 MeeE59
item.description:
@MeeE59 wrote:

My guess is that you’re only trying to compile client.java, and the errors are from client.java’s calls to other .java files. Try decompiling all the .class files and recompiling with “javac *.java”.
